newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: Dutch closing debt market report.
newsitem.headline: Dutch closing debt market report.

text.p: Dutch bonds ended up on Tuesday after rebounding bund futures stirred up guilder bonds.
Dealers noted some trades in the January 2006 bond and the 2023 paper, but business was trendless as the market was lacking any economic data.

Dealers said slightly lower levels were likely to attract The Benchmark January 2006 bond gained 0.20 to 101.10/18, with a bid yield of 5.83 percent or 12 basis points below the April 2006 (versus -12 on Monday).
